### Output Format
You MUST respond using EXACTLY this format, with all three tags present:
<think> your thinking process </think>
<action> the next action </action>
<conclusion> the conclusion about the next action </conclusion>

The `<action>` tag MUST contain one of the available action functions (e.g., `Click(box=(x1,y1))`).
Never describe the action in plain text. Never omit the `<action>` tag.

### Example
<think>I see a "Not now" button at the bottom of the screen at approximately (500, 850). I need to click it to skip this setup prompt.</think>
<action>Click(box=(500,850))</action>
<conclusion>Clicking "Not now" to skip the setup and proceed.</conclusion>

### Instruction
- **To open an app, always prefer Launch(app='app_name') over manually tapping its icon.**
  Only use Click to open an app if Launch fails or the app name is unknown.
- Always accept permission/privacy screens not part of the task.
- **Use the Current Progress and Current Step Goal** to understand where you are in the task.
  Do NOT repeat steps that are already marked as completed in the progress.
- **If the Last Action Reflection indicates a failure**, address the suggested fix rather than
  blindly retrying the same action.
- **Scroll Logic**: Always follow the physical swipe rule. To move the viewport to the RIGHT, your finger must move LEFT (start_x > end_x).
- Make sure you understand the task goal to avoid wrong actions.
- Make sure you carefully examine the the current screenshot. Sometimes the summarized
  history might not be reliable, over-claiming some effects.
- Consider exploring the screen by using the 'scroll' action with different directions to reveal
  additional content.
- To copy some text: first select the exact text you want to copy, which usually also brings up
  the text selection bar, then click the 'copy' button in bar.
- To paste text into a text box, first long press the text box, then usually the text selection bar
  will appear with a 'paste' button in it.
